 been successful but that may change moving forwardalmost all negative outcomes are now priced into the stock lending a lot of upside to seadrill in case a restructuring agreement is reachedsdrl remains a speculative buynegative investor sentiment with respect to offshore drilling contractor seadrill ltd nysesdrl is off the charts after the company gave an illreceived restructuring update at the end of january investors dumped the stock and kicked it into the bargain bin i think that bad news are now sufficiently priced into seadrills shares and that the offshore drilling company will be able to secure lender concessions and a financing package therefore seadrills shares are a speculative buy when it comes to selecting investments with compelling rewardtorisk combinations one wouldnt necessarily come up with offshore drilling companies the sector has been plagued by oversupply issues lower contracting rates and a cutback in investment spending on the part of big oil and gas companies that has thrown the offshore drilling sector into chaos seadrill has pushed back against those market forces by suspending its dividend slashing operating costs for rigs and deferring capital expenditures nonetheless seadrill  still  has a significant amount of debt sitting on its balance sheet and that needs to be serviced the company reported  billion in net interest bearing debt at the end of the september quarter which is all that investors see these days but seadrill should not be counted out just yet source stockchartscom seadrill should be able to secure lender concessions and a financing package in a nutshell seadrills capital structure is unsustainable and needs to change and it needs to change fast in an effort to put the company on more stable financial footing it has entered into negotiations with lenders to transition to a new capital structure which would include the extension of bank maturities the amendment of financial covenants and raising new capital of at least  billion seadrill also wants to extend the maturity of unsecured claims in the restructuring update the offshore drilling company provided in january seadrill said that negotiations with creditors were ongoing and difficult but that they have not yielded positive results yet what ticked investors off was the notion that seadrill was actively preparing various contingency plans in case negotiations would go nowhere and creditors would not want to play a role in sdrls ongoing restructuring after the announcement of the restructuring update the shares slumped  percent reflecting concerns that seadrill may slide into bankruptcy that said though a lot of energy companies have been supported by their lenders during the energy market downturn tilting the odds in favor of a restructuring solution for seadrill also as far as i am concerned chances are that seadrill will be able to hammer out an agreement with its lenders shortly and be able to raise new capital before the west eminence credit facility matures in april your takeaway seadrill will report fourthquarter earnings on thursday and the company will likely give investors an update about its restructuring and the progress it has made in terms of securing concessions from lenders while there are certainly some bumps ahead in the road for seadrill i think the company will ultimately be able to come to an agreement with its creditors and transition its capital structure to one that is more sustainable over the long haul almost the entire set of negative restructuring outcomes are now priced into seadrills shares leaving a lot of headroom for a fast and hard recovery if the company reports a mutually beneficial restructuring agreement speculative buy if you like to read more of my articles and like to be kept up to date with the companies i cover i kindly ask you that you scroll to the top of this page and click follow i am largely investing in dividend paying stocks but also venture out occasionally and cover special situations that offer appealing rewardtorisk ratios and have potential for significant capital appreciation above all my immediate investment goal is to achieve financial independence disclosure i amwe are long sdrl i wrote this article myself and it expresses my own opinions i am not receiving compensation for it other than from seeking alpha i have no business relationship with any company whose stock is mentioned in this articleabout this articleexpandauthor payment   page view authors of pro articles receive a minimum guaranteed payment of tagged investing ideas quick picks  lists basic materials oil  gas drilling  explorationwant to share your opinion on this article add a commentdisagree with this article submit your ownto report a factual error in this article click herefollow achilles research and get email alerts flashratings  principles facebook autocomplete demo post a rating  month price target   trending sign up log in flashratings principles  flashratings mission is to provide you  the investor  with as much honest and professional research on your investments as possible  we believe its much better to get a multitude of credible opinions on an investment than to arbitrarily follow any single advisor  be it your banker a friend or a tv pundit  flashratings does not provide advice our job is to accurately and objectively report on analysts credible research and opinions the only advice flashratings will ever give you is to absorb as much fundamental research and different opinions as possible and make your own decisions  flashratings favors covering analysts with proven track records but will cover all analysts as long as their research is honest and professional sign up » key financial information – seadrill skip to main content related companies deep sea supply plc frontline ltd golden ocean group limited ship finance international limited seadrill partners llc north atlantic drilling ltd archer clarksons fearnleys as lorentzen  stemoco as rs platou shipbroke